checkForIdField

protected FieldContext checkForIdField()
                                throws UnableToCompleteException
Tries to find information about an mapped id. First the modelType is scanned for an XmlId annotation. If there's no such annotation the XmlReader is asked whether it contains an XmlId annotation inside an XmlFields annotation. If one of them was found the corresponding FieldContext is created and returned.

If more than one XmlId annotation was found in the modelType an UnableToCompleteException is thrown.

If no id mapping was found (neither in the modelType nor inside the XmlFields annotation) null is returned.

Returns:
the FieldContext for the id mapping or null if no id mapping is present.
Throws:
UnableToCompleteException - if more than one XmlId annotation was found in the modelType
